File: platform/cli/src/commands/start.ts, line ~204.

Current code:
```
console.log(pc.dim(`${pad}pointing to ${mcpUrl} with Authorization: Bearer <secret>`));
```

The `secret` parameter is already in scope (passed to `printMcpClientConfigs`). When `secret` is non-null, interpolate it directly:
```
console.log(pc.dim(`${pad}pointing to ${mcpUrl} with Authorization: Bearer ${secret}`));
```

When `secret` is null (unlikely in practice but the type allows it), use a generic message without a misleading `<secret>` placeholder:
```
if (secret) {
  console.log(pc.dim(`${pad}pointing to ${mcpUrl} with Authorization: Bearer ${secret}`));
} else {
  console.log(pc.dim(`${pad}pointing to ${mcpUrl} with an Authorization: Bearer header`));
}
```

Also add a hint about retrieving the secret later, e.g.:
```
console.log(pc.dim(`${pad}Run ${pc.bold('opentabs config show --show-secret')} to see MCP client configuration at any time.`));
```

This function is also used by `platform/cli/src/commands/config.ts` (handleConfigShow with --show-secret), so the fix benefits both call sites.
